history.content:
As a rising sophomore declared EECS, how necessary is it that I take EE16A this upcoming semester? I'm 141 on the waitlist but the discussion/lab that I'm waitlisted for are full. I've read a lot of posts saying it's unlikely I'll get into the class if the discussions/labs are full, but I need EE16A/EE16B in order to start taking upper divs.

If I'm forced to wait until spring semester to take EE16A, would I still be on track for EECS?
history.subject: Waitlist for EE16A
